a simple shell script collection to build openstreetmap maps for garmin devices

installation:
-------------

- create a .conf file in the conf directory (copy and motify the .example file)
- get mkgmap and mkgmap splitter jars or build it via mkgmap-suite_get.sh script
- set the correct mkgmap and splitter path

usage:
------

for a standard map without anything special simple run:

./osm-build_map.sh

for a outdoor map run:

./osm-build_map.sh -c austria -t outdoor
